</div><div id="body_t1_cvx" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Is that meant to be an anti-rational quote?</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_cvx"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_cvx" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_cvx')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_cvx" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_cvx')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_cvx" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/g1/rationality_quotes_may_2009/cvx?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_cvx" href="#cvf" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_cvx" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_cvx')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_cvx class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_cvx" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_cvx" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_cvx" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_cwc" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_cwc" class="parent"><a name="cwc" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_cwc" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_cwc" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_cwc" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Nominull/">Nominull</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">20 May 2009 12:55:51AM</span><span class="votes " >9 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_cwc'] = ['8 points', '9 points', '10 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_cwc')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_cwc" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_cwc" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Nominull/">Nominull</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">20 May 2009 12:55:51AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_cwc'>9 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_cwc'] = ['8 points', '9 points', '10 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_cwc')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_cwc" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Only if you think violence is never justified ;)</p>

<p>It's a warning to rationalists, especially Hollywood Mister Spock type rationalists, that even though promoting true beliefs is a charitable act on par with patching up someone's slashed tires, people will often take rather unkindly to it.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_cwc"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_cwc" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_cwc')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_cwc" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_cwc')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_cwc" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/g1/rationality_quotes_may_2009/cwc?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_cwc" href="#cvx" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_cwc" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_cwc')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_cwc class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_cwc" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_cum" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_cum" class="parent"><a name="cum" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_cum" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_cum" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_cum" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Kaj_Sotala/">Kaj_Sotala</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 May 2009 07:31:34PM</span><span class="votes " >5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_cum'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_cum')">[+] (7 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_cum" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_cum" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Kaj_Sotala/">Kaj_Sotala</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 May 2009 07:31:34PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_cum'>5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_cum'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_cum')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_cum" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>...look at 9/11 tower destruction theories. They want to believe something other than the planes caused the buildings to collapse. OK fine, let them bark up that tree if they want, but why must they leap to bizarre stories about government agents and secret operations? None of that is necessitated by the idea that another mechanism was fully or partially responsible. Why don't they suspect that Al-Quaeda planted a bomb in the basement in order to hasten the building's collapse, as a secondary part of their operation? Why leap to the US government as the culprit? Why not suspect that there was a flaw in the building construction, and that the blueprints don't reflect it because the building contractor covered it up? Why not suspect Martians? They create an incredibly open-ended doubt into which you could plug anything, and then they fill this void with (you guessed it) a story, with completely arbitrary elements.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>-- <a href="http://bbs.stardestroyer.net/viewtopic.php?p=3086186#p3086186" rel="nofollow">Mike Wong</a></p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_cum"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_cum" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_cum')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_cum" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_cum')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_cum" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/g1/rationality_quotes_may_2009/cum?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_cum" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_cum')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_cum class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_cum" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_cum" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_cum" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_cv6" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_cv6" class="parent"><a name="cv6" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_cv6" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_cv6" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_cv6" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/dclayh/">dclayh</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 May 2009 09:12:01PM</span><span class="votes " >7 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_cv6'] = ['6 points', '7 points', '8 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_cv6')">[+] (6 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_cv6" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_cv6" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/dclayh/">dclayh</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 May 2009 09:12:01PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_cv6'>7 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_cv6'] = ['6 points', '7 points', '8 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_cv6')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_cv6" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>That quote seems silly.  If there were hidden elements to 9/11 (or JFK, or anything) obvious enough for lone nuts to find, then it's reasonable to assume the government investigation would have found them also.  Given that the government investigation didn't say anything about it, then, it's reasonable to assume it's because they have something to hide.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_cv6"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_cv6" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_cv6')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_cv6" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_cv6')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_cv6" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/g1/rationality_quotes_may_2009/cv6?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_cv6" href="#cum" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_cv6" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_cv6')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_cv6 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_cv6" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_cv6" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_cv6" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_d8c" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_d8c" class="parent"><a name="d8c" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_d8c" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_d8c" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_d8c" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/brian_jaress/">brian_jaress</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 May 2009 01:01:50AM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_d8c'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_d8c')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_d8c" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_d8c" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/brian_jaress/">brian_jaress</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 May 2009 01:01:50AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_d8c'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_d8c'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_d8c')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_d8c" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Since we're doing quotes:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Never attribute to malice that which can be adequately explained by
  stupidity.</p>
  
  <p>-- Hanlon's Razor</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Of course, once you start thinking in terms of stories instead of
theories, it's easy to forget that only a tiny fraction of things that
happen are the result of planning or motive.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_d8c"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_d8c" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_d8c')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_d8c" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_d8c')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_d8c" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/g1/rationality_quotes_may_2009/d8c?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_d8c" href="#cv6" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_d8c" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_d8c')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_d8c class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_d8c" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_cv7" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_cv7" class="parent"><a name="cv7" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_cv7" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_cv7" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_cv7" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/SoullessAutomaton/">SoullessAutomaton</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 May 2009 09:19:34PM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_cv7'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_cv7')">[+] (4 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_cv7" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_cv7" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/SoullessAutomaton/">SoullessAutomaton</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 May 2009 09:19:34PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_cv7'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_cv7'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_cv7')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_cv7" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Also, there's the obvious, cynical "<em>cui bono?</em>" point. The government is one of the few entities that could reasonably be said to have benefitted from the attacks (expanded power, pretense for war, &amp;c.), so if you start with the assumption that the "official story" is wrong the government would be the next most plausible culprit.</p>

<p>The argument used is much more applicable to creationist arguments of the form "evolution has this flaw, ergo god exists".</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_cv7"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_cv7" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_cv7')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_cv7" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_cv7')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_cv7" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/g1/rationality_quotes_may_2009/cv7?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_cv7" href="#cv6" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_cv7" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_cv7')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_cv7 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_cv7" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_cv7" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_cv7" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_cva" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_cva" class="parent"><a name="cva" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_cva" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_cva" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_cva" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/dclayh/">dclayh</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 May 2009 09:29:48PM</span><span class="votes " >8 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_cva'] = ['7 points', '8 points', '9 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_cva')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_cva" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_cva" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/dclayh/">dclayh</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 May 2009 09:29:48PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_cva'>8 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_cva'] = ['7 points', '8 points', '9 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_cva')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_cva" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I heard an interview with the guys who do South Park that for their 9/11 conspiracy episode they were considering making the real culprits the American flag manufacturers, because they clearly benefited the most.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_cva"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_cva" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_cva')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_cva" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_cva')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_cva" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/g1/rationality_quotes_may_2009/cva?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_cva" href="#cv7" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_cva" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_cva')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_cva class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_cva" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_cva" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_cva" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_cvc" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_cvc" class="parent"><a name="cvc" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_cvc" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_cvc" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_cvc" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/SoullessAutomaton/">SoullessAutomaton</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 May 2009 09:31:39PM</span><span class="votes " >9 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_cvc'] = ['8 points', '9 points', '10 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_cvc')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_cvc" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_cvc" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/SoullessAutomaton/">SoullessAutomaton</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 May 2009 09:31:39PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_cvc'>9 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_cvc'] = ['8 points', '9 points', '10 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_cvc')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_cvc" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>American flag manufacturers</p>
